@node "Main" "BetterBalance.mcc 11.1"
@{jcenter}@{par}
@{b}@{u}BetterBalance.mcc 11.1 - Copyright © 08-Jun-1998 by Maik "bZ!" Schreiber@{uu}@{ub}@{par}

@{jleft}BetterBalance.mcc is a subclass of Balance class which allows the programmer
to easily save and load all balance settings of a GUI.@{par}

See the supplied demonstration program for more details.@{par}


@{jcenter}Please visit @{b}The IQ Computing Web Site @{ub}at @{b}www.IQ-Computing.de@{ub}@{par}


@{" License          " link "License.txt/Main"}@{par}

@{" Requirements     " link "Requirements"}@{par}

@{" History          " link "History" 9999}@{par}

@{" Author           " link "Author"}@{par}
@{" Acknowledgements " link "Acknowledgements"}@{par}


Note: This document makes heavy use of OS 3.1 @{amigaguide} commands.@{par}

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{par}
  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}@{par}

BetterBalance.mcc requires at least version 3.0 of MUI (V11).@{par}
It is recommended that you always use the latest version of MUI.@{par}

@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@{par}
  @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}@{par}

11.0, 07-Apr-1998:@{par}
@{lindent 4}  - first version of BetterBalance.mcc@{lindent 0}@{par}

11.1, 08-Jun-1998:@{par}
@{lindent 4}  - if an object has a MUIA_HorizWeight and/or MUIA_VertWeight of 0, its
horizontal and/or vertical weights will not be loaded upon
MUIM_Application_Load@{lindent 0}@{par}
@{lindent 4}  - made some small internal improvements@{lindent 0}@{par}

@endnode

